Germany Says Too Early to Discuss Changes to Greek Bailout

-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 
2011-09-28T12:16:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/germany-says-too-early-to-discuss-changes-to-greek-bailout.html
Germany  isn’t “putting pressure on
anyone” to accept additional losses on Greek sovereign bonds as
part of the planned second bailout for the debt-laden country,
Finance Ministry spokesman  Bertrand Benoit  said.  “It’s way too early to talk about this,” he said by phone
today. “We want to take everything one step at a time and the
priority now is the sixth tranche” of  Greece ’s current aid
package.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tony Czuczka at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net  